{
  "text": "the most discriminative directions are most probably lying in the subspaces generated from S w and S b . Researchers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] have investigated the null space of S w , denoted by null(S w ), and the range space of S b , denoted by range(S b ), using analytical methods. It can be proved that the solution to (4) lies in these subspaces. We will use the EDFE algorithm to search for discriminant projection directions in null(S w ), range(S w ), and range(S b ), respectively, and compare their discriminability in recognizing faces. In this section, we present a method to calculate these three spaces. If some other subspace is considered, it is only needed to take its basis as the original basis of the search space. Before proceeding to the detailed method of calculating the basis for null(S w ), range(S w ), and range(S b ), we first give the definitions of these three subspaces as follows",
